<l>Such <foreign xml:lang="ta">meṉṟoṭarmoḻi</foreign><note place="foot">I.e. if we have a sequence ' [long demonstrative |<foreign xml:lang="ta">yā
          +</foreign> nasal + plosive + overshort <foreign xml:lang="ta">-u</foreign>] + plosive ',
          then the plosive is lengthened (doubled), e.g. <foreign xml:lang="ta">āṅku-k-koṇṯāṉ,
          yāṅku-k-koṇṯāṉ.</foreign></note> which begin with the lengthened form of</l>
<l>demonstrative roots, or such interrogative <foreign xml:lang="ta">meṉṟoṭarmoḻi</foreign> [which</l>
<l>begin] with <foreign xml:lang="ta">yā</foreign> do not deviate from the rules of the plosives [being</l>
<l>doubled].</l>
      </lg>
